took%20our%20twin%20sons%20to%20the%20US%20from%20Australia%2C%20they%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-surprised-my-welsh-kids-when-they-visited-the-us-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esurprised%20by%20how%20different%20things%20were%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlmost%20immediately%20after%20arriving%2C%20while%20driving%20into%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-that-surprised-brit-visiting-la-for-first-time-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edowntown%20Los%20Angeles%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20airport%2C%20they%20were%20surprised%20at%20the%20sheer%20number%20and%20variety%20of%20fast-food%20chains%20along%20the%20highway.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-never-do-in-australia-from-woman-lives-there%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAustralia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we%20have%20several%20major%20fast-food%20chains%2C%20but%20our%20sons%2C%20Charlie%20and%20Thomas%2C%20couldn't%20believe%20how%20many%20different%20chains%20there%20were%20in%20the%20US.%20They%20were%20surprised%20that%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20dozens%20of%20different%20burger%20chains%2C%20fried%20chicken%20restaurants%2C%20and%20fast%20food%20joints.%20We%20let%20them%20pick%20one%20to%20try%2C%20and%20they%20chose%20the%20iconic%20In-N-Out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce352ec4-d0b4-44c6-b616-9eca2bfd3d2b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20couldn't%20understand%20why%20all%20the%20dollar%20bills%20looked%20the%20same%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20Australian%20bill%20is%20a%20different%20color%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20distinguish.%20Charlie%20and%20Thomas%20were%20surprised%20that%20every%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-dollar-bill-evolution-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20dollar%20bill%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20looked%20the%20same.%20This%20concerned%20them%2C%20as%20they%20were%20worried%20they%20would%20accidentally%20hand%20over%20a%2020-dollar%20bill%20instead%20of%20a%20one-dollar%20one%20and%20lose%20money.%20I%20solved%20this%20by%20only%20giving%20them%20one-dollar%20bills.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20had%20a%20problem%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flowest-state-and-local-sales-tax-ranked-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20being%20added%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20cash%20register%20which%20they%20weren't%20used%20to.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetermined%20to%20maximize%20their%20spending%2C%20they%20were%20frustrated%20by%20the%20pricing%20system.%20In%20Australia%2C%20the%20price%20displayed%20is%20the%20final%20price%20(including%20tax%20and%20tip)%2C%20so%20they%20found%20it%20challenging%20to%20determine%20what%20an%20item%20would%20cost.%20We%20explained%20they%20needed%20to%20add%20tax%20(and%20occasionally%20a%20tip)%2C%20but%20the%20differing%20state%20taxes%20necessitated%20using%20a%20calculator%20each%20time%2C%20which%20diminished%20their%20shopping%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e19c344-bd3f-4ce0-9097-19e055e706de%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20asked%20to%20repeat%20themselves%20annoyed%20them%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20believe%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrities-who-dont-haveamerican-accents-in-real-life-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAussie%20accents%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20very%20strong%2C%20but%20many%20Americans%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20understand%20Charlie%20and%20Thomas%20and%20were%20often%20asked%20to%20repeat%20themselves.%20A%20few%20people%20even%20asked%20if%20they%20were%20speaking%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20hate%20tomatoes%2C%20so%20when%20ordering%2C%20they%20always%20ask%20for%20%26quot%3Bno%20tomatoes.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20they%20pronounce%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bto-mah-to%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20how%20Americans%20pronounce%20it%2C%20often%20leading%20to%20confusion.%20Another%20word%20that%20caused%20an%20issue%20was%20water%2C%20which%20we%20pronounce%20%26quot%3Bwar-ta.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20they%20had%20learned%20to%20say%20tomatoes%20and%20water%20in%20an%20American%20accent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fdddc615-5b58-4a8e-a217-c7df9898153b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fast%20food%20novelty%20eventually%20wore%20out%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20surprising%20conversation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20traveled%20across%20several%20states%2C%20we%20endeavored%20to%20eat%20healthy%20food%20but%20found%20this%20a%20challenge%20among%20the%20spate%20of%20cheap%20(but%20generally%20fried)%20fast%20food%20options.%20Midway%20through%20our%20second%20week%20of%20vacation%2C%20Charlie%2C%20who%20loves%20his%20junk%20food%20and%20is%20known%20for%20avoiding%20vegetables%2C%20shocked%20me.%20While%20choosing%20where%20to%20eat%2C%20he%20turned%20to%20my%20wife%20and%20me%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan%20we%20please%20go%20somewhere%20with%20vegetables%20and%20where%20the%20food%20isn't%20fried.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20stunned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f1019fb-252f-4d1d-93fa-5958111eeff2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20thing%20that%20stood%20out%20to%20them%20was%20the%20patriotism%20of%20Americans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20our%20visit%2C%20they%20remarked%20on%20the%20number%20of%20houses%20and%20businesses%20that%20proudly%20displayed%20the%20American%20flag%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20rare%20to%20see%20an%20Australian%20flag%20outside%20an%20official%20place%20back%20home.%20We%20also%20attended%20a%20f