ef%20of%20staff%2C%20said%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BWar%20on%20the%20Rocks%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-superiority-only-possible-short-bursts-us-air-force-officer-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%20in%20January%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20given%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20a%20given%20for%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Gen.%20James%20Hecker%2C%20the%20commander%20of%20NATO's%20air%20command%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-stand-in-missile-air-superiority-defenses-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%20He%20said%20NATO%20hadn't%20been%20serious%20about%20fighting%20Russia%20since%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20but%20the%20military%20alliance%20was%20taking%20steps%20to%20strengthen%20its%20air%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can't%20get%20air%20superiority%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20doing%20the%20fight%20that's%20going%20on%20in%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Hecker%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20know%20how%20many%20casualties%20that%20are%20coming%20out%20of%20that%20fight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20initial%20Russian%20attack%20could%20surprise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20failed%20to%20execute%20a%20decisive%20shock-and-awe%20blow%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20NATO%20can%20expect%20the%20same%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20a%20vastly%20tougher%20enterprise%20against%2032%20states%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20armed%20with%20advanced%20fighter%20jets%20and%20air-defense%20networks%2C%20than%20it%20was%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20air%20force%20can't%20meet%20Western%20air%20forces%20air%20to%20air%20in%20a%20major%20attack%20without%20being%20%26quot%3Bshot%20to%20pieces%2C%26quot%3B%20Bronk%20said.%20But%20that's%20not%20all%20that%20Russia%20brings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russians%20could%20attempt%20a%20surprising%20and%20impactful%20opening%20attack%2C%20experts%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Russians%20could%20target%20vulnerabilities%20like%20satellites%20to%20try%20to%20disrupt%20the%20space-based%20communications%20and%20navigation%20NATO%20airpower%20depends%20upon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223729%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20pair%20of%20Russian%20Sukhoi%20Su-35%20fighters%20fire%20missiles%20in%20Russia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634e9bb10dfcda409666275%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222491%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia%20has%20a%20number%20of%20capable%20jets%2C%20Su-35s%20like%20the%20ones%20seen%20firing%20missiles%20here%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20as%20a%20collection%20of%20dozens%20of%20nations%2C%20NATO%20has%20the%20superior%20air%20combat%20capabilities.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FMaxim%20Shemetov%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20Russia%20made%20%26quot%3Ba%20dash%20for%20the%20Baltic%20republics%2C%20for%20example%2C%20in%20the%20first%20few%20hours%20or%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20for%20Western%20air%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20Fabian%20Hinz%2C%20an%20IISS%20missile%20expert%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20nightmare%20scenario%2C%20the%20Baltic%20states%20would%20need%20NATO%20airpower%20to%20stop%20a%20large%20Russian%20combat%20force%20from%20advancing%2C%20and%20the%20greatest%20threat%20to%20that%20endeavor%20likely%20would%20not%20be%20Russia's%20air%20force%20but%20other%20capabilities%2C%20such%20as%20its%20air%20defenses.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20could%20be%20expected%20to%20use%20any%20aerial%20sanctuary%20to%20attack%20the%20Baltic%20defenders%20and%20inbound%20NATO%20troops%20with%20the%20drone%20and%20glide-bomb%20attacks%20it%20has%20used%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20menace%20Western%20Europe%20with%20an%20even%