0of%20NATO.%20An%20air%20base%20centralizes%20fuel%20and%20munitions%20storage%2C%20spare%20parts%20to%20repair%20planes%2C%20and%20the%20mechanics%20and%20air-traffic%20controllers%20who%20keep%20flight%20operations%20running.%20Dispersal%20increases%20the%20challenge%20of%20keeping%20all%20these%20airfields%20supplied%20and%20may%20spread%20its%20talent%20too%20thinly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20intelligence%20officer%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20said%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Ba%20cultural%20thing%20that%20most%20Western%20air%20forces%20are%20used%20to%20operating%20from%20centralized%20bases.%26quot%3B%20But%20he%20advocated%20for%20a%20shift%20in%20how%20the%20West%20treats%20aircraft%20and%20command%20centers%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Blining%20them%20all%20up%20to%20get%20whacked%20is%20not%20really%20an%20option.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENATO's%20next%20move%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20war%20where%20the%20much-larger%20and%20more-powerful%20NATO%20faces%20off%20against%20Russia%20would%20look%20different%20from%20Ukraine's%20fight.%20But%20experts%20said%20the%20West%20must%20invest%20in%20its%20militaries%20now.%20Russia%20may%20be%20deterred%20if%20the%20West%20appears%20strong%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBronk%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20so%20much%20cheaper%20and%20easier%26quot%3B%20to%20invest%20now%20in%20the%20capabilities%20to%20deter%20Russia%20than%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bto%20actually%20invest%20in%20the%20forces%20capable%20of%20fighting%20an%20extended%20war%20for%20six%20months%2C%20a%20year%2C%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20NATO%20needs%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F5953405f-d91a-4598-8b6b-6345452ca328%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20its%20air-defense%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20the%20alliance's%20eastern%20flank%2C%20where%20member%20states%20have%20said%20they%20could%20be%20the%20first%20ones%20targete